Biographies

  • Björk biography

    Through her eclectic avant-garde pop infused with electronica, Björk (born November 21st, 1965) has become an international icon with her intelligent, forward-thinking music that frequently defies expectation.

    Read more
  • Kaskade biography

    Twice voted ‘America’s top DJ’ by the DJ Times and one of the key proponents in the revival of American Progressive House, Kaskade is seen as a pretty important figure in Dance Music.

    Read more
  • BANKS biography

    BANKS (born 15 June 1988) aka Jillian Rose Banks is an up and coming R&B singer-songwriter hailing from California, US.

    Read more
  • ODESZA biography

    ODESZA are an exciting duo originating from Seattle US. They produce enlightening records which push the boundaries of electronic music, and conjure up energetic melodies which are easy to love.

    Read more

  • Unknown Mortal Orchestra biography

    Unknown Mortal Orchestra, formed in 2010 by Ruban Nielson, is a psychedelic and lo-fi rock band, hailing from Portland, Oregon, U.S. and Auckland, New Zealand.

    Read more
  • Squarepusher biography

    Squarepusher (born January 17, 1975) is the stage and performing name of Tom Jenkinson, an British experimental drum and bass electronic music artist, hailing from Chelmsford, Essex, UK.

    Read more
  • Oneohtrix Point Never biography

    Daniel Lopatin (b. 1982) known as Oneohtrix Point Never is a musician, composer, producer, and label founder of Software Recording Company living and working in Brooklyn, New York.
